{"questionId":"15096","questionHtml":"<div class=\"qb-parent-stem\"><p>A survey was conducted on a group of people. The first question asked how many pets they each own. The results are summarized in the following table.</p>\n<p style=\"text-align:center;\"><img src=\"__IMG__/13bcf8629029051648a4e81f7f4b8bc2dab213f3.png\"></p></div>\n<div class=\"qb-parent-stem\"><p>The second question asked each member of the group to state their age and preferred pet. The data obtained is organized in the following table.</p>\n<p style=\"text-align:center;\"><img src=\"__IMG__/fcfc94019a71850a127818d8e2c70865363e826d.png\"></p></div>\n<div class=\"qb-parent-stem\"><p>A <span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"{\\chi ^2}\">\n  <mrow>\n    <msup>\n      <mi>χ</mi>\n      <mn>2</mn>\n    </msup>\n  </mrow>\n</math></span> test is carried out at the 10 % significance level.</p></div>\n<div class=\"qb-leaf-prompt\"><p>Calculate the expected number of teenagers that prefer cats.</p></div>","markschemeHtml":"<p><span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"\\frac{{85 \\times 55}}{{160}}\">\n  <mfrac>\n    <mrow>\n      <mn>85</mn>\n      <mo>×</mo>\n      <mn>55</mn>\n    </mrow>\n    <mrow>\n      <mn>160</mn>\n    </mrow>\n  </mfrac>\n</math></span>&nbsp; <strong>OR&nbsp;&nbsp;</strong><span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"\\frac{{85}}{{160}} \\times \\frac{{55}}{{160}} \\times 160\">\n  <mfrac>\n    <mrow>\n      <mn>85</mn>\n    </mrow>\n    <mrow>\n      <mn>160</mn>\n    </mrow>\n  </mfrac>\n  <mo>×</mo>\n  <mfrac>\n    <mrow>\n      <mn>55</mn>\n    </mrow>\n    <mrow>\n      <mn>160</mn>\n    </mrow>\n  </mfrac>\n  <mo>×</mo>\n  <mn>160</mn>\n</math></span>&nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;<em><strong>(M1)</strong></em></p>\n<p>29.2 (29.2187…)&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; <em><strong>(A1)(G2)</strong></em></p>\n<p><strong><em>[2 marks]</em></strong></p>","meta":{"questionI